Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that, I'd like to introduce my hubby, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.08,0:00:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Bum, bum, bum, bum, bum, bum, bum, bum, bum, bum, bum, bum.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.46,0:00:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she's raised me right, you can tell that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.10,0:00:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, today we're talking about, today we're talking about practical spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.67,0:00:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So we, how many people here are new?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.29,0:00:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How many new people?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.14,0:00:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wave your hand, I can't see unless you wave it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.35,0:00:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wave, wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.18,0:00:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.70,0:00:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.21,0:00:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So that gives me an idea how much time to spend.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.10,0:00:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How much time to spend on review.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.66,0:01:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I like to do a quick review to refresh people's memory of what we've been talking about for the last few years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.06,0:01:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And for new people, to give them an orientation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.92,0:01:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Sedona group, you know, is usually people who've been here before.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.00,0:01:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't spend a lot of time on review.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.78,0:01:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But we show you where the review is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.20,0:01:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you have any questions, you can holler.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.31,0:01:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When we do the review.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.10,0:01:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've got any kind of a question, you can just put your hand up and holler.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.80,0:01:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And Susan will call on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.94,0:01:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see where you are, and I just hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.78,0:01:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.12,0:01:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So just put up your hand and wave if you've got a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.86,0:01:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we're going to do a quick review that will take us through all the previous lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.82,0:01:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We're putting out a book of, a collection of all the slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.10,0:01:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All the lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.24,0:02:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we realized that when you play a DVD, it doesn't, you know, it doesn't show up with sufficient clarity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.70,0:02:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, you know, the camera's quite away from the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.18,0:02:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's hard to read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.70,0:02:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So this way we have it flip over.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.36,0:02:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can flip over and follow what is on the screen in the DVD.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.43,0:02:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll start then with a quick review of the slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.93,0:02:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,To bring us up to date.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.15,0:02:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We always start with a map of consciousness as a common point of reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.03,0:02:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,As a common point of reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.29,0:02:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,These are levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.07,0:02:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,These are emotional states.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.51,0:02:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,These are attitudes all boiled into one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.69,0:02:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we see the view of yourself and how you understand God.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.71,0:02:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We should have.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.93,0:02:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Society in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.47,0:02:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How you view society.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.68,0:02:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The levels are called peace, joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.13,0:03:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They go all the way down to pride and anger and hatred and disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.93,0:03:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.80,0:03:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.15,0:03:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And the log of it tells us the relative power.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.34,0:03:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be because these are exponential levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.56,0:03:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, even a rise of a few points makes a considerable difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.37,0:03:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The emotion that's along with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.37,0:03:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll talk more about that later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.58,0:03:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see many that predominate in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.15,0:03:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of hatred and, of course, political contests such as the one we're currently involved in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.34,0:03:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to bring out the worst in mankind, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.28,0:04:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It brings up all kinds of trivialities that we make fun of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.14,0:04:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And hatred gets, this is a time for hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.75,0:04:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And what people forget is that, I use the example of strawberry versus vanilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.43,0:04:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,See, if you pick strawberry, it doesn't mean you have to hate vanilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.78,0:04:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.37,0:04:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You can pick vanilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.57,0:04:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to hate strawberry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.27,0:04:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.04,0:04:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You can just pick what you pick.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.86,0:04:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to hate the other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.75,0:04:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.81,0:04:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but people like an excuse for hatred, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.24,0:04:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They love a hate parade.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.18,0:04:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Protests, protests, protests.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.31,0:04:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,People love a hate parade.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.50,0:04:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to deprive them of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.07,0:04:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Once every four years, they can hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.75,0:04:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They can hate without feeling guilty about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.45,0:04:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They can feel patriotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.81,0:04:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Patriotic about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.36,0:04:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, it's hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.69,0:05:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it'll be over before long.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.01,0:05:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll all survive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.87,0:05:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Every four years, we go through this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.42,0:05:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.68,0:05:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So the slides for today, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.21,0:05:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.80,0:05:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We're doing a quick review.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.15,0:05:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So we do the map of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.43,0:05:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the next one we do is any questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.40,0:05:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Any questions on any of these slides?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.34,0:05:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You just holler and put your hand up, and we will try to answer it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.30,0:05:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Those lights sort of fade out the slides, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.44,0:05:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's one reason for putting out a collection of slides,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.24,0:05:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is because now if you see this on a DVD, I can hardly see it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.40,0:05:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you read it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.54,0:05:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So this way, if we put the slides out so you can flip over on them at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.40,0:05:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,an explanation of the world's dilemma is shown by this graph,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.32,0:06:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that 85% of the world's population calibrates below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.36,0:06:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we know that 200 is the level of integrity and truth and reliability
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.64,0:06:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the capacity to really comprehend truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.28,0:06:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern the difference between appearance and essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.34,0:06:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 is falsehood and allness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.40,0:06:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is negative in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.44,0:06:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And 200 and up is all that is positive in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.50,0:06:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's dismaying is the notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.34,0:06:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the mass of the world's population.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.96,0:06:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of the world's population calibrates below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.12,0:06:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,85%.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.80,0:06:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Cannot tell the difference between truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.92,0:06:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They cannot tell the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.88,0:06:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.40,0:06:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Same to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.22,0:06:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a child, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.18,0:06:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, honey, this is arsenic and this is candy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.02,0:06:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the arsenic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.50,0:06:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Arsenic tastes sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.76,0:06:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ever eat any arsenic?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.96,0:07:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to poison somebody, you put it in the dessert.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.40,0:07:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're an enemy for dinner, and he eats the dessert, and he goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.18,0:07:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and as he goes down, you say, it was in the dessert.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.22,0:07:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was in the plum pudding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.78,0:07:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of the world's population explains many phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.22,0:07:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead of feeling depressed and upset,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.40,0:07:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the world's conditions in various places,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.46,0:07:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you just recall that the majority of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.54,0:07:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is unable to discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.24,0:07:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Unable, inherently unable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.00,0:08:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like a person with an IQ of 60, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.92,0:08:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,can't get through postgraduate, college, and university.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.38,0:08:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so now the next one is, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.42,0:08:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the consequence of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.28,0:08:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.40,0:08:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The consequence of this is that although the majority
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.74,0:08:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world's population calibrates below 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.62,0:08:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,those that calibrate above 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.36,0:08:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,which is only 15% of the world's population,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.20,0:08:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,their power is so enormous that they counterbalance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.48,0:08:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So 85% of the world is counterbalanced by 15% of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.30,0:08:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that is capable of discerning truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.82,0:08:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there are people that lead and sustain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.39,0:08:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They sustain not by what they do, but by what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.15,0:08:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A group like this doesn't have to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.50,0:09:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't do anything to save the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.63,0:09:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody promise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.60,0:09:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do anything to save the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.31,0:09:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Please give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.89,0:09:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You just be what you are to the fullest extent that you can be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.93,0:09:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And by doing that, you're fulfilling your destiny to the old.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.37,0:09:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,By being what you can be to the ultimate then,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.10,0:09:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the subject of today's lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.10,0:09:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To be all that you can be to the fullest extent
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.96,0:09:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is already fulfilling your obligation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.86,0:09:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and doing more than any kind of good-hearted doingness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.75,0:09:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,can do for the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.48,0:09:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So this 15%, merely by being what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.72,0:09:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,By merely being what they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.37,0:09:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you see this 15% outweighs this 85%.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.37,0:09:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If that were not so,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.00,0:09:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind would have self-destructed centuries ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.39,0:10:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The sheer mass of negativity would have destroyed all of human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.43,0:10:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So a group like this has a very important function.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.62,0:10:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think we've calibrated before
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.51,0:10:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,how many people this group, just this group sitting here, offsets.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.37,0:10:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.58,0:10:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.62,0:10:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This group offsets on the negative side
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.43,0:10:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 50 million people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.79,0:10:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,100 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.58,0:10:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,150 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.15,0:10:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,200 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.22,0:10:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,175 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.60,0:10:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hundreds of millions of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.25,0:10:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because the power goes up exponentially.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.39,0:10:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Exponentially.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.12,0:10:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, a group like this offsets
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.36,0:10:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the negativity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.55,0:10:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the negativity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.79,0:10:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the negativity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.86,0:10:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the negativity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.89,0:10:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the negativity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.91,0:10:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the negativity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.94,0:10:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the negativity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.96,0:10:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the negativity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.98,0:10:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the negativity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.37,0:10:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,literally of millions of people
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.08,0:10:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,just by what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.58,0:10:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do to help the world
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.46,0:10:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to the greatest extent possible
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.05,0:11:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is breathe in and out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.08,0:11:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody able to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.34,0:11:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.98,0:11:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,With your head knocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.63,0:11:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.86,0:11:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.77,0:11:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Me breathing again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.03,0:11:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.91,0:11:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.36,0:11:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.58,0:11:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.67,0:11:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Percent of elapsed time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.13,0:11:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This has to be brought up to date.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.29,0:11:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's sitting on my desk waiting for me
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.93,0:11:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring it up to date.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.67,0:11:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The percent of elapsed time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.25,0:11:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrated consciousness level of man,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.15,0:11:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of elapsed time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.60,0:11:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, consciousness is only shot up
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.91,0:11:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in very, very recent times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.17,0:11:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost like yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.46,0:11:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really only yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.86,0:11:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that we moved from the dinosaur,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.37,0:11:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.72,0:11:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.13,0:11:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.67,0:11:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If we align these with the earth epics,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.10,0:11:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the slow evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.10,0:12:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,over actually millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.53,0:12:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions and millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.12,0:12:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Cambrian period,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.70,0:12:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Devonian period,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.29,0:12:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,all these fancy sounding names.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.67,0:12:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.36,0:12:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,at a,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.37,0:12:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,at a snail's pace over millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.62,0:12:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we have the various forms of life
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.60,0:12:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that occurred at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.43,0:12:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, there was only bacteria and algae.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.37,0:12:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And they calibrate as one and two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.37,0:12:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we see the beginning of the fishes and the reptiles
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.74,0:12:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.82,0:12:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,up through the mammalian until present day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.39,0:12:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.24,0:12:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.75,0:12:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we have the animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.15,0:12:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.05,0:12:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the entire thing displayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.51,0:12:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the octopus, our old friend, the octopus.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.46,0:13:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And the old friend, the Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.05,0:13:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Don't go walking barefoot in his cage, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.03,0:13:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have the snake, the alligator,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.13,0:13:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the whale, the dolphin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.00,0:13:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think it's just fascinating to look
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.13,0:13:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,at the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.29,0:13:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we have a certain commonality
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.13,0:13:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.37,0:13:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always look at all animals as friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.62,0:13:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Even those that are not friendly,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.87,0:13:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I consider them friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.00,0:13:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they share, they share animal existence
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.55,0:13:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and animal consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.75,0:13:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's an intuitive understanding that goes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.79,0:13:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're wide awake, you have an intuitive understanding of where
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.56,0:13:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,an animal is at.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.26,0:13:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that bear is dangerous, you intuit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.36,0:13:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And you slowly say, bye, bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.06,0:13:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye, bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.86,0:14:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye, bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.26,0:14:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So we love the animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.70,0:14:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the pleasures of human life
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.30,0:14:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is the loving of the animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.06,0:14:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody who loves animals, of course, is helping the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.04,0:14:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because love uplifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.80,0:14:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.22,0:14:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Uplifts mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.12,0:14:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told you, I had patients that lived alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.18,0:14:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And they were so self-centered and depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.16,0:14:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told them that I would not treat them unless you get
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.27,0:14:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a canary, or a kitty, or a doggy, or a puppy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.00,0:14:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you're only concerned about you,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.10,0:14:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't really help you much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.80,0:14:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The big me, that's all you're concerned about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.66,0:14:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Me, me, me, me, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.66,0:14:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you can't even take care of a couple of snails,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.06,0:14:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or goldfish, I mean, something other
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.22,0:14:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,than your own wonderful, marvelous self.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.32,0:14:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No, there are people that can't even take care of a goldfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.34,0:14:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so they're stuck where they're stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.46,0:15:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And there they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.08,0:15:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we see the animals that we have learned to love.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.44,0:15:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've got to know them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.72,0:15:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We've gotten to know Coco, the trained gorilla,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.66,0:15:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and that wonderful gray parrot, who is actually, at 400,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.56,0:15:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,able to comprehend.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.22,0:15:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the parrot I have at home is, what is that one calibrated at?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.24,0:15:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget we calibrated her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.86,0:15:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the calibration of her?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.80,0:15:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what's her name that bird?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.77,0:15:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.44,0:15:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.00,0:15:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.34,0:15:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,300.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.39,0:15:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,350.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.98,0:15:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,340.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.25,0:15:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,350.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.06,0:15:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have an African great, calibrates at 340 right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.18,0:15:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're sitting there quietly, and all of a sudden,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.32,0:15:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.04,0:15:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.13,0:15:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.20,0:15:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.10,0:15:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.52,0:15:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.75,0:15:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.56,0:15:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.52,0:15:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.80,0:15:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.32,0:16:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have the delight, the delight of the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.37,0:16:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about the delight of awareness of your own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.64,0:16:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The delight in the beauty of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.03,0:16:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The delight in just the effect of your own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.25,0:16:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The delight that you share existence and consciousness with the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.81,0:16:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fun to walk in the woods by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.12,0:16:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's twice as much fun to walk in the woods with a doggie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.89,0:16:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.13,0:16:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's sharing, so to share.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.74,0:16:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,With another person, it's more fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.83,0:16:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Or with a kid, it's more fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.33,0:16:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Even with a doggie, it's more fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.86,0:16:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Or with a horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.42,0:16:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Even lead a horse along.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.60,0:16:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,At least there's somebody sharing the world with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.98,0:16:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Without animals, mankind would not have existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.86,0:16:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't have survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.66,0:16:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he didn't have the strength to plow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.16,0:16:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He needed a horse to plow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.32,0:17:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't have milk without the cow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.34,0:17:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't have wool without the sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.32,0:17:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Began to realize he didn't have meat without killing the deer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.75,0:17:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't have clothing without the hide and the pelts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.90,0:17:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And he wouldn't have shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.56,0:17:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the world without plastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.38,0:17:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So to delight in your own existence means to share the awareness of the divinity of existence itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.08,0:17:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,To exist is already a tremendous miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.04,0:17:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have here the dog's wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.90,0:17:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a wagging tail at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.88,0:17:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody is studying, a member of our group here is studying advertising.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.42,0:17:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you can calibrate the power of an advertisement.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.08,0:18:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And he found that if you put a little dog in the corner of the advertisement with a wagging tail,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.42,0:18:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of the advertisement like quadruples.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.38,0:18:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Quadruples.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.48,0:18:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the way to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.88,0:18:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What we do at friends is to wag your tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.28,0:18:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And purr.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.72,0:18:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.94,0:18:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.36,0:18:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are all fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.84,0:18:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We've fallen in love with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.22,0:18:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of us follow them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.20,0:18:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Alex, the trained African gray parrot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.40,0:18:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oscar the cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.30,0:18:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oscar is that cat that can tell when somebody's due to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.50,0:18:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.04,0:18:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, within 72 hours, if this,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.98,0:18:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's a cat or was it a dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.66,0:18:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.75,0:18:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Oscar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.40,0:18:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If you see Oscar coming to sleep with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.92,0:19:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Oscar.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.64,0:19:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Oscar.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.40,0:19:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.90,0:19:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see the fascination that man has had with his animal friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.16,0:19:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So we view other people as friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.82,0:19:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We view animals as friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.06,0:19:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We view all of nature as friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.60,0:19:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And that way, that helps us to live in a positive awareness of our,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.51,0:19:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of our self and the reality of our own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.94,0:19:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.46,0:19:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget how many we got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.80,0:19:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I better hurry on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.14,0:19:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.40,0:19:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Great Books of the Western World is significant for people that are,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.54,0:19:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, students of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.22,0:19:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Because here you find the answer to what goes on with society currently,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.70,0:19:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as for some centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.60,0:20:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the calibration of the intellectual foundation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.00,0:20:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of Western world is in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.94,0:20:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Great Books of the Western World, this is the product
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.98,0:20:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of man's best thinking over the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.10,0:20:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It runs all the way up to 480, all the way to 505.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.70,0:20:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwin at 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.70,0:20:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Descartes, 490.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.18,0:20:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Engels goes down quite a bit, 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.18,0:20:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's one that calibrates the lowest of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.12,0:20:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.00,0:20:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.94,0:20:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What's his first name, Marx?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.18,0:20:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.34,0:20:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.27,0:20:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl Marx?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.29,0:20:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That Marx?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.18,0:20:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.00,0:20:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That Marx at 130 slipped in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.40,0:20:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And that Marx is the downside of current society
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.94,0:21:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the Marxian dialectic has been reframed verbally
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.38,0:21:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and now appears as various.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.68,0:21:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are a number of theories,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.92,0:21:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,all of which calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.18,0:21:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.44,0:21:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So that we see is one of the intellectual disasters
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.62,0:21:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind, intellectual.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.32,0:21:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And that people cannot tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.74,0:21:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And these things, of course, sound seductive,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.12,0:21:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,sound seductive, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.74,0:21:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You have nothing to lose but your chains.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.74,0:21:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Bang, bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.92,0:21:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And it always makes for a great parade, a great parade.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.58,0:21:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.98,0:21:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get T-shirts with this hero freeing the oppressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.09,0:21:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are the oppressed in today's society?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.18,0:22:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the oppressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.98,0:22:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you realize you're the oppressed?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.88,0:22:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Which way is society going?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.70,0:22:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.98,0:22:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's leaving spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.29,0:22:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to secular, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.75,0:22:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.36,0:22:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Society is moving away from this tradition in the back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.98,0:22:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's moving more towards atheistic socialism, Marxism.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.22,0:22:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.92,0:22:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fallen decline of the Western civilization,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.24,0:22:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which is pointed out, of course, by the Pope as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.62,0:23:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is due to leaving one field of a high energy level
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.59,0:23:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and moving to a lower one by popularization.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.88,0:23:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.16,0:23:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.96,0:23:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.88,0:23:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's going on, you know, politically in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.02,0:23:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.26,0:23:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So the next one is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.54,0:23:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.40,0:23:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The muscle test response,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.68,0:23:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which we've spoken about and explained many times,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.58,0:23:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,has many explanations.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.68,0:23:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A biologic one, that it was necessary for survival,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.36,0:23:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,for primitive organisms to be able to tell that which is true and healthy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.60,0:23:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,from that which is poisonous and false.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.76,0:23:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's moved all the way through now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.10,0:23:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have an explanation from quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.76,0:23:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the observation which led to calibrating the levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.62,0:23:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,was quite simple, quite simple.
