Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.75,0:27:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,alright we've done it over 7,000 times
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.81,0:27:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,well you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.91,0:27:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to get some sleep in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.24,0:27:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway we do it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.83,0:27:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,whenever so we find it very
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.77,0:27:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,pragmatically useful
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.22,0:27:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,very pragmatically useful
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.75,0:27:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so we've explained
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.59,0:27:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the collapse of the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.74,0:27:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,wave function and advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.50,0:27:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,theoretical physics
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.59,0:27:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and the book Mindful Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.98,0:27:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,by Henry Stapp
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.93,0:27:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,professor of physics at Berkeley
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.22,0:27:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,gives a rational explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.81,0:27:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not necessary to know
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.01,0:27:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,any of this therefore forget it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.98,0:27:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,go to the next slide
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.81,0:27:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,alright just take my word for it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.55,0:27:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.93,0:27:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,physiologic basis which is
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.83,0:27:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,very important also
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.24,0:27:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you see 85% of the population
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.03,0:27:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot tell truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.61,0:27:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and one of the reasons is
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.63,0:27:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to do with cerebral dominance
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.93,0:28:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.74,0:28:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you process things
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.33,0:28:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.81,0:28:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,this level below 200
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.77,0:28:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or above 200
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.31,0:28:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,processes things differently in the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.01,0:28:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,one reason people at this level
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.96,0:28:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,can't comprehend this level
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.11,0:28:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is because you have to use
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.79,0:28:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,this side of the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.53,0:28:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,this side
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.31,0:28:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,side of the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.77,0:28:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,has a very positive effect
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.67,0:28:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,positive emotions
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.70,0:28:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and releases very importantly
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.67,0:28:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,endorphins
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.98,0:28:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the endorphins are
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.41,0:28:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,peaceful
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.57,0:28:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,harmonious
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.09,0:28:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,peaceful harmonious
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.75,0:28:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,pleasant. And one of the benefits of spiritual endeavor is that you shift more and more over
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.16,0:28:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to the endorphins, which are releasing hormones, which do play their part in altering how you see
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.75,0:28:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and experience the world. It's hard for a person dominated by the left brain to see the world as
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.16,0:29:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,friendly. And for a person dominated by the right brain, it seems rather simple. To a right-brained
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.22,0:29:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,person, they say, well, you walk around Sedona, it's lovely, and the weather is great here, and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.44,0:29:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,mountains are gorgeous, and I mean, what more do you want? A person very far in the left brain
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.75,0:29:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,says it's too hot around here, and they charge too much, and the restaurants all rip you off.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.40,0:29:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no parking place. I mean, you know, you see the negative view of the world, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.14,0:29:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,see the negative view of the world versus the positive view of the world. It's all the same
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.30,0:29:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,world, so it's just perception. We'll go on to the next one. The correlation of loads of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.62,0:29:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness with social problems is of considerable sociologic import. Politically
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.20,0:29:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,unpopular, too, because the cause of things, the conditions that precipitate them, people
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.92,0:29:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,have a political position about.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.14,0:30:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that these consequences are caused from without instead of from within, instead of from
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.86,0:30:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,within. We see that the incidence of problems of all kinds, from poverty to crime, to the suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.54,0:30:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,rate, the homicide rate, the rate of in prisons, the higher the level of consciousness, the rate
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.10,0:30:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of unemployment is zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.14,0:30:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of poverty is zero. Happiness is 100%. And the rate of criminality is zero. So people
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.10,0:30:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,who are spiritually highly motivated and caring and care about their fellow human beings,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.48,0:30:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,care about life in general, have a positive, uplifting viewpoint. Therefore, the level
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.42,0:30:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness, the higher it goes, the rate of unemployment drops eventually to zero,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.82,0:30:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and poverty unhappens.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.86,0:31:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Unhappiness disappears. So what we have then, we're left with people who are of extremely low
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.70,0:31:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness for reasons that are karmic, biologic, sociological as well. And you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.32,0:31:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,reach people where the rate of unemployment is as close to 100%. The rate of poverty is 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.90,0:31:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Rate of happiness is zero percent. And criminality is common. The current economic
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.86,0:31:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,crisis was due to trusting that people would have this kind of a reliability. If the government
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.82,0:31:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,guarantees their mortgages, anybody and everybody could have one. So all the people from here
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.04,0:31:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,flew into the mortgages, they instantly stopped paying them. They stopped cleaning out the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.62,0:31:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,attic, they stopped sweeping the sidewalk, and the thing went into poverty collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.30,0:31:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there is no reliability here. You see this?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.79,0:32:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not for any other reason other than the level of consciousness itself. The level
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.89,0:32:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness. In a high level of consciousness, you make sure that everything gets paid, taken
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.00,0:32:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,care of, cleaned up, tidied up. The screens are put on in the summer, and the storms are
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.83,0:32:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,put on in the winter. It seems obvious. But there are whole populations where it does
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.55,0:32:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,not even occur. And I used to own some rental properties back east, and I had some of those
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.79,0:32:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,people living there.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.79,0:32:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't deserve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.79,0:32:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't deserve it. I didn't deserve it. I didn't deserve it. I didn't deserve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.79,0:32:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't discover it until too late. Anyway, I had rented this lovely gatehouse, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.09,0:32:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,an English Tudor slate roof. All brick, gorgeous place. For a pittance. And this guy was living
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.44,0:32:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,there and I noticed that the garbage never seemed to go out. So one day I went by to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.25,0:32:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,see how he was doing, and I just knocked on the door and he was sitting at the kitchen
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.01,0:32:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,table, and all over the kitchen table was marijuana. And he was... I said, how are things
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.91,0:32:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,going, Pete?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.37,0:33:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.79,0:33:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does all the garbage go that should be out by the side of the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.65,0:33:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, well, I don't know, maybe over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.13,0:33:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went and opened the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.59,0:33:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the door to the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.55,0:33:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire basement was filled, a fill, halfway up the stairway with trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.85,0:33:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What he did with trash, old grapefruit rinds and garbage and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.20,0:33:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is he just opened the door of the basement and threw it down there,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.62,0:33:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and he closed the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.72,0:33:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He got a mortgage, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.84,0:33:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, people want an explanation of what is the current economic situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.22,0:33:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.29,0:33:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's missing that the lovable consciousness is going to,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.98,0:33:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.20,0:34:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,tell you how reliable a contract is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.58,0:34:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,People here pay a great deal of attention to contracts.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.08,0:34:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, you know, that's a contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.51,0:34:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We agreed to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.42,0:34:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And people here say, oh, that's a contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.24,0:34:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, wipe your feet on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.28,0:34:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right, we'll move to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.46,0:34:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of happiness, and here we have
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.65,0:34:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,a correlation of levels of consciousness and rate of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.98,0:34:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And here you see the log of the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.98,0:34:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and the rate of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.77,0:34:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, spiritual endeavor tends to, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.27,0:34:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,pull you higher and higher on this map.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.19,0:34:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And you reach a level where your only complaint is you're never unhappy
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.87,0:34:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've got nothing to complain about.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.03,0:34:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't got anything to complain about.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.65,0:35:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How can people control you if you've got nothing to complain about?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.07,0:35:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what they do is they pick on your complaints
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.27,0:35:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and play them up and make political hay out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.44,0:35:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the rate of happiness goes up based not on externals,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.87,0:35:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,how much money you have, whether you went to college,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.33,0:35:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,any of those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.63,0:35:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's based solely on one's level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.98,0:35:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it seemed to me the most efficient way to improve your life overall,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.65,0:35:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is to pursue advancing your level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.39,0:35:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you increase your rate of happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.92,0:35:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you increase your productivity,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.01,0:35:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's beneficial to yourself and everybody around you,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.33,0:35:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,including the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.27,0:35:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.15,0:35:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.01,0:35:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where we are on the slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.98,0:35:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have a quick review of spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.71,0:35:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,People often write me from all over the world
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.59,0:35:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and want to know about a certain spiritual teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.85,0:35:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And I tell them how to find out what that teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.30,0:35:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what that teacher calibrates at themself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.51,0:36:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I also point out that here's over a hundred spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.20,0:36:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.53,0:36:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And next we'll have the writings of these teachers are calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.86,0:36:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And somehow they always find somebody in the middle of nowhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.34,0:36:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,honky-donker, who claims to be the descendant of the master of Wahamahe,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.44,0:36:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and suggests that we turn over all our material goods to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.18,0:36:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And would you advise that I are following him?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.68,0:36:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, well, I've already done enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.14,0:36:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've told you how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.76,0:36:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next slide?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.40,0:36:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.48,0:36:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the great avatars of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.86,0:36:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Christian apostles at 980.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.96,0:36:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This has to do with the relics, the realm of the relics,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.42,0:36:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,calibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.30,0:36:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrated at 900.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.16,0:37:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that the bones underneath the Basilica in Rome calibrate over 900.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.56,0:37:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It just affirms the spiritual level of the 12 apostles.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.53,0:37:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And John the Baptist, Moses, Abraham, St. Paul, Muhammad,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.98,0:37:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and Muhammad after age, later age.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.56,0:37:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.30,0:37:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Great spiritual writings.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.24,0:37:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So when people are lost or confused, I say, look, here you've got 100 teachers
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.68,0:37:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and well over 100 books,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.56,0:37:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and any one of these will take you a lifetime to really work it through.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.30,0:37:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So this will take care of the next 40 or 50 lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.51,0:37:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When you come back, work on this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.72,0:37:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when you come back again, come work on this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.18,0:37:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you get to the bottom here,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.30,0:37:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to come back anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.76,0:38:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When you finish the Zohar, that catapults you right off the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.56,0:38:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Shot out into infinite space by the Zohar,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.86,0:38:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates at 905.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.08,0:38:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.38,0:38:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,See, some people start with this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.26,0:38:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people start there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.88,0:38:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You can start anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.74,0:38:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.10,0:38:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think this is a very handy reference because,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.86,0:38:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,this kind of diagnostic work has never been done before.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.51,0:38:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the value of the work is that we're able to learn things
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.72,0:38:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that mankind has never had a chance to verify.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.88,0:38:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always been the authority of religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.80,0:38:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the authority of the good book,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.72,0:38:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the authority of the Torah, the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.22,0:38:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So belief then was based on authoritarianism.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.64,0:38:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That led to many people becoming atheists.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.86,0:39:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the authority, the institutions themselves made serious errors over the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.46,0:39:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And consequently, just one error and a doubter can say,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.76,0:39:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,well, any organization that does so-and-so can't know the truth about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.53,0:39:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they might know the truth about 98% of the things
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.32,0:39:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and not know the truth about 2%.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.96,0:39:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is very practical, very practical.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.53,0:39:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see a major division,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.44,0:39:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,even in the capital,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.14,0:39:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,even in the capital,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.28,0:39:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the calibration of the Christian Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.01,0:39:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's the Lompsa Bible or the King James Version.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.76,0:39:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference between the King James Version
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.42,0:39:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Lompsa Bible is considerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.22,0:39:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where the Lompsa Bible is on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.82,0:39:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.50,0:39:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But anywhere in the Lompsa Bible, it was in the 600s, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.64,0:39:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see it, sweetheart?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.36,0:39:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The King James Version calibrates in the high 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.46,0:39:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,475.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.19,0:39:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here's the Lompsa right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.86,0:40:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Right in front of my eyeballs.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.26,0:40:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No one's not going to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.34,0:40:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.59,0:40:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.94,0:40:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.67,0:40:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.24,0:40:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.01,0:40:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends on whether, you know, you leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.03,0:40:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends on whether you leave the New Testament in or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.44,0:40:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.51,0:40:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, the Lompsa Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.46,0:40:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it calibrates higher than the King James Version.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.57,0:40:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if one says it's in the New Testament,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.88,0:40:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to know whose translation.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.74,0:40:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the Lompsa is from the Aramaic,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.78,0:40:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the more common one is from the Greek.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.96,0:40:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So the translation from the Greek calibrates less than the one from
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.55,0:40:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the Eastern, so-called Eastern manuscripts of the Eastern Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.08,0:40:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.48,0:40:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Fashionable philosophies.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.24,0:41:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This has to do with moral equivalency and all kinds of things
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.03,0:41:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that we see flash across the television screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.03,0:41:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of bizarre things.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.40,0:41:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech, of course, which is now supplanted God and divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.55,0:41:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.68,0:41:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.18,0:41:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of World War II, calibrated at 255,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.62,0:41:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,free speech in the U.S. as of currently is 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.94,0:41:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So free speech then, due to the media,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.36,0:41:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is now focused on popularization and appeal
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.58,0:41:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and dramatization rather than truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.26,0:41:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.10,0:41:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech then is the railroad.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.32,0:41:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It was theoretically the railroad to freedom,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.58,0:42:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but in practice is the railroad to the collapse of our own society.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.90,0:42:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If falsehood has equal privilege with truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.82,0:42:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,then what would hold up the columns of our society?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.74,0:42:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So the New York Times, for instance, New York Times,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.94,0:42:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to even calibrate where the New York Times is right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.84,0:42:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I better not calibrate the New York Times.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.32,0:42:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course, they'll have an editorial.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.44,0:42:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.24,0:42:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like it's 140 standard.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.42,0:42:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.20,0:42:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they vary.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.68,0:42:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, right now, the New York Times is probably,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.86,0:42:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,let's just do it one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.66,0:42:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.66,0:42:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do the New York Times.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.96,0:42:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do the New York Times.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.50,0:42:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates currently over 170.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.00,0:42:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,165.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.98,0:42:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,160.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.32,0:42:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The New York Times calibrates at 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.00,0:43:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that say about the prognosis of American society?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.60,0:43:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The banking system collapses.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.80,0:43:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The New York Times calibrates at 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.03,0:43:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we seeing the fall and collapse of Western civilization?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.36,0:43:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.01,0:43:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,When I grew up, the New York Times probably calibrated around 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.32,0:43:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was growing up, the New York Times calibrated over 400 of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.44,0:43:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,405.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.40,0:43:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The New York Times calibrated at 400 when I was growing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.18,0:43:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it calibrates at, what did we say?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.94,0:43:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,God, we don't want the comedies to hear about that.
